Description: Lé Vibe — Code OSS–based IDE with managed local Ollama
 Lé Vibe is a Linux desktop product (Phase 2) built on open-source editor
 components, with hardware-aware Ollama model setup and a dedicated-port
 managed ollama serve lifecycle. This skeleton package ships the Python
 bootstrap and launcher; the Code - OSS binary is provided separately or via
 LE_VIBE_EDITOR (e.g. VSCodium).
 .
 After install, read /usr/share/doc/le-vibe/README.Debian for quick steps,
 Continue wiring, workspace .lvibe/ memory consent (PRODUCT_SPEC §5), and
 Phase 2 scope vs editor fork / alternate bundles (spec-phase2 §14 — H7 packaging/flatpak + packaging/appimage; same file, Authority).
 .
 Monorepo clone / CI: README.Debian summarizes build-le-vibe-ide pre-binary
 ide-ci-metadata.txt (upload-artifact retention-days; workflow permissions
 contents read + actions write for checkout + artifacts) and GitHub Actions Summary
 LE_VIBE_EDITOR pointers (editor/BUILD.md).
 .
 Sibling le-vibe-ide .deb and full-product maintainer flow: README.Debian and
 docs/PM_DEB_BUILD_ITERATION.md (packaging/scripts/build-le-vibe-debs.sh --with-ide;
 Full-product install on success).
